:: Question 1:4:2 {"position":"2475,1525","size":"100,100"}
"So tell me a bit about the others who live... unlive? Unlive here. I’d like to know some more about them if I stay here."
    
Damien’s smile thins a bit, face masked in a guarded expression. "In due time," he responds. His eyes betray that he knows exactly what I’m doing, but thankfully he doesn’t push me on the whole ‘cause of death’ thing. "Some of the residents here are... skittish. And I take their privacy seriously. Rest assured that if you don’t care for them when you meet them, you may always leave. There is no contract of residence here."
        
That statement didn’t fill you with confidence.

[[Continue.|Question 2:1]]
<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 2:2:1 {"position":"1400,1900","size":"100,100"}
"Oh, I lived in a pretty small place, split the rent with a couple of roommates," you say.
    
You pause, but Damien continues to stare expectantly at you. You clear your throat and continue, "I didn’t know them very well, and they moved out a couple of weeks after I woke up, so..."
    
"I understand," Damien says, interrupting you. He paused for a moment before asking, "How did you find it, your old living situation?"

