:: Question 3:1 {"position":"2200,2150","size":"100,100"}
<<if $DamienOpinion gte 1>>"Alright, just one more question." Damien straightened up in his chair, his tone going more serious than before. "Say y-" He stops mid sentence, looking down at his notebook, furrowing his brow before closing the notebook and looking back towards you.

"$name... I wish to be frank with you. We have all died, and death is inherently traumatic. We all have demons we face, and the residents of this house are no different. But sometimes, needs clash. Sometimes what is helpful for one is harmful to another, and conflict arises. How would you deal with this conflict?"

[["Kick out whoever is causing trouble." (Aggressive)|Question 3:2:1 Aggressive]]
[["...I wouldn’t." (Nervous)|Question 3:2:1 Nervous]]
[["Try to calm down whoever is in crisis and go from there." (Confident)|Question 3:2:1 Confident]]
[["Sit with whoever is having a rough time and let them vent to me." (Cheerful)|Question 3:2:1 Cheerful]]<<else>>"Alright, just one more question." Damien straightened up in his chair, his tone going more serious than before. "Say you moved in. Say there was a crisis of somesort in the house. How would you handle it?"

[["Figure out who’s causing trouble and deal with them directly." (Aggressive)|Question 3:2:2 Aggressive]]
[["What kind of crisis?" (Nervous)|Question 3:2:2 Nervous]]
[["Can you elaborate?" (Confident)|Question 3:2:2 Confident]]
[["Talk to everyone and figure out what I can do to help." (Cheerful)|Question 3:2:2 Cheerful]]<<endif>>

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Intro 2 Aggressive {"position":"2000,775","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $aggressive += 1>>
<<endsilently>>This whole situation is just... frustrating. There's only a handful of safe places in this city to haunt and they’re all scooped up by groups of ghosts like this one. Now you have to ‘prove’ to this guy that you’re worthy of living in his broken down mansion. You are certainly not relishing in the idea of an afternoon spent being dissected and judged before having someone else decide whether you’re decent enough to have a place to stay.
    
Still, being hauntless is... not an option. And at least this Damien guy was willing to hear you out, to even consider letting you move in. Several of the other haunted places had very territorial tenants.
 
[[Continue.|Explore 1 Option]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 1:4 Aggressive {"position":"2000,1400","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $aggressive += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"That information is mine, and mine alone," you say, teeth clenched in frustration. "I will not have the circumstances of my death determine the entire course of my unlife."
    
You can feel your fist shaking as they are clenched in your lap. Damien looks taken aback, and far more animated than you’ve seen him before. It seems he wasn’t expecting that reaction. He should have been.
    
"I... I apologize. I meant no offense," he stammers, feeling just how quickly he lost control of this situation.
    
The silence stretches on for just a moment too long. Finally, the keeper speaks up again:
    
"Let’s just... move on with the interview." You nod tersely, feeling the muscles already stiff in your neck from the tension. Who knew ghosts could get stiff muscles?

[[Continue.|Question 2:1]]
<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


