:: Endings {"position":"2125,4150","size":"100,100"}
Damien nods and looks between the other three ghosts. You nervously await his decision.

<<if $DamienOpinion gte 2>>If your heart could beat it would be pounding. Damien stands, briefly phasing through the table before stepping to the side. Hands clasped in front of him, he announces his decision.

"I am very pleased to welcome you to the house properly." Damien says, a smile growing with each word. You look at him for a moment, and then your gaze shifts to the other ghosts, finding them all smiling at you.

Finally, he says, "Welcome home."

END<<else>><<if $AhmadOpinion gte 1 and $JuniaOpinion gte 1 and $LydiaOpinion gte 1>>If your heart could beat it would be pounding. Damien stands, briefly phasing through the table before stepping to the side. Hands clasped in front of him, he announces his decision.

"I... truly am sorr-"

"Now, hold on a minute." Ahmad interrupts Damien, who looks genuinely surprised.

"This ghost seems perfectly pleasant to me." he continues.

"T-to me as well," Junia adds, though so quiet that you almost didn't notice."

"Agreed." Lydia adds. You look between the three other ghosts in astonishment.

"See," Ahmad continues. "This is why you should involve the others in these decisions. Everyone seems fine with letting them in. So if you're so worried about everyone's comfort, then listen to us now. Let this new ghost in."

Stunned, Damien looks towards the other two, who both nod in affirmation. Finally, he turns to you.

"I... suppose I was too harsh. In that case... welcome."

END<<else>><<if $aggressive gte 4>>If your heart could beat it would be pounding. Damien stands, briefly phasing through the table before stepping to the side. Hands clasped in front of him, he announces his decision.

"I... truly am sorry." He looks away for a moment to collect his thoughts. "You seem decent enough, but the state of the house is... precarious. I wish you all the best."

You scoff. He said no. Shocker.

"Yeah, I don’t think so."

"What?" Damien looks genuinely shocked.

"I may be ‘newly dead,’ but I am aware that ghosts can’t actually touch each other. You can’t make me leave."

"I-"

You stand up, Damien and the other ghosts looking on in concern, horror. "Gonna go pick out my new room, //housemates//." You can feel a smile break out across your face. You  stand and start to walk out of the room, the others looking on, stunned.

"I think I’ll like it here..." you say as you walk away.

...

And so you settle in, a ghost in the home of ghosts, haunting the haunted.

END<<else>>If your heart could beat it would be pounding. Damien stands, briefly phasing through the table before stepping to the side. Hands clasped in front of him, he announces his decision.

"I... truly am sorry." He looks away for a moment to collect his thoughts. "You seem decent enough, but the state of the house is... precarious. I wish you all the best."

You stand, wordlessly, and walk through the door into the night.

END<<endif>><<endif>><<endif>>
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Ending 4 {"position":"2275,4150","size":"100,100"}
"This place... if this interview was meant to evaluate me, then it gave me a good look into how you run things. I don’t want to be a part of it."

"Oh?" Damien looks genuinely surprised.

"Yeah," your eyes narrow. "Keep your gated community or whatever. I don’t need it."

You stand, wordlessly, and walk through the door into the night.

END

<img src="images/ghostleaving.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1 Option {"position":"2200,900","size":"100,100"}
You look around at the front yard – desolate trees and piled leaves of orange, red, and brown,disturbed slightly by the autumn wind. Part of you wants to get this over with, to just go up to the door and do the interview. But another part – fueled by nerves, dread, or curiosity, you aren't sure – compels you to take a look around. Unsure, you stand at the precipice, a few feet away from the steps, and make your decision.

[[Walk up to the door|Question 1:1]]
[[Walk around the house's perimeter|Explore 1:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:1 {"position":"3200,525","size":"100,100"}
You turn away from the steps and the door, towards the left, and begin to walk clockwise around the perimeter of the house. The world is eerily quiet. You find that the lack of your own footfalls unsettles you the most. You keep expecting to hear the crunch of leaves as you drift around the all too still house.

The manor is impressively large, far more so than it appeared from the front. But as large as it is, the disrepair is obvious. Many of the windows you pass seem to lead to collapsed rooms; many sections of roof are open to the sky.

[[Continue.|Explore 1:2]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:2 {"position":"3200,650","size":"100,100"}
As you walk, you realize you're looking less and less at the house, and more ahead of you, at the surroundings, or even at your own feet. You gather your thoughts as you walk. This place... it's nicer than some of the other spots you tried, but a far cry from what you were hoping for. You may not have to worry about the cold or the rain, but a half destroyed house isn't exactly the most welcoming. Was this really where you wanted to live? maybe you could find something better if you kept looking? Then again, this is the only place that was already occupied and was still willing to let you talk to them. Maybe this is the best available?

Still, you could do this 'interview' and see what happens. You had time to figure this all out. If there was anything you had in abundance now, it was time.

[[Continue.|Explore 1:3]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:3 {"position":"3200,775","size":"100,100"}
Your gaze wanders across patchy roofs and empty windows– you stop in your tracks, looking back to find the window you just passed is not as empty as you expected. It stands on the third floor of the building, in a section that looks to be in better condition than the rest. In the frame is a younger looking man – dark brown skin, short cropped hair, and deep dark eyes which gaze back at you from his perch high up in the house. He's dead; you know this. Not only has the house been abandoned for as long as anyone can remember, but you've found that some part of you instinctively knows when you're looking at a fellow ghost or at the living.

The man smiles, his eyes scrunching up in genuine happiness, and excitedly waves to you.
<<set $seenAhmad to true>>
[[Wave back|Explore 1:4:1]]
[[Stay still|Explore 1:4:2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:4:1 {"position":"2950,900","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>A slight smile tugs at your lips as you wave back at the figure. Perhaps this place wouldn't be so bad after all. Not many of the ghosts you've met until this point have been particularly friendly. This person, on the other hand, seems downright excited to see you.

He turns his head from the window, likely hearing something from inside the house. Turning back to you, he smiles and nods before walking off, leaving you alone staring at the house.

[[Continue.|Explore 1:5]]
<img src="images/man waving at ghost.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:4:2 {"position":"3450,900","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion -= 1>>
<<endsilently>>Guarded, you eye the figure warily, and do not wave. After a moment, his face falls a bit, and he slowly lowers his hand back to his side. What was his game? It's not like the people who live in the house were particularly thrilled to have you, hence the whole 'interview process'. So what was gained by acting as if you were a welcomed guest.

The man in the window scrunched his face up in confusion, seemingly trying to figure you out as well. After a moment, he simply frowns, and turns to leave, leaving you alone staring at the house.

[[Continue.|Explore 1:5]]
<img src="images/manhouse.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:5 {"position":"3200,1025","size":"100,100"}
"Ahem"

You jump, startled by the sudden sound. Turning quickly around you find a tall figure in a moth-eaten charcoal suit. He’s gaunt, tan skin and dark hair, with eyes that never seem quite fully focused. Still, he looks like he died quite young. You wonder how long ago that was.

"Ah, $name, I see you’ve met Ahmad." he says, in a voice all too reminiscent of a creaking door hinge. Damien, the self proclaimed ‘Keeper’ of this haunted mansion. You’ve met him only once before, when you first found this place. It was him who suggested you come back today to interview for one of the open rooms in the house.

[[Continue.|Explore 1:6]]
<img src="images/damien.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:6 {"position":"3200,1150","size":"100,100"}
"Uh, yeah," you answer, all too eloquently. You're still recovering from the fright of having Damien sneak up on you. Turns out it's rather easy to do when your footfalls make no sound. "I take it he's one of the other ghosts who live here?"

"Indeed," Damien replies, turning around and gesturing for you to follow him. You comply, falling into step with him as the two of you walk back around the house, towards the front entrance.

"How many other ghosts live here?" you ask.

"There are four, including myself and Ahmad. If all goes well today, you will have a chance to meet them."

You nod, steeling yourself for the actual reason you've come: the interview.

[[Continue.|Explore 1:7]]
<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 1:7 {"position":"3200,1275","size":"100,100"}
It isn't long before the two of you make it back to the front steps, and find yourselves face to face with the door once more. Damien strides purposely towards it, getting a few steps ahead of you as you stop to take a breath. He turns around to face you.

"Please, come inside," he said, gesturing for you to follow as he walks backwards through the door. You follow – albeit reluctantly as you still haven’t quite adjusted to walking through solid objects – and find yourself inside the manor. You turn to find Damien already sitting at a small tea table off to the right of the entryway. You walk over to join him, before hesitantly starting to phase through the legs of the table and the armrest of the chair to try and sit. Noticing your hesitancy, Damien offers, "You won’t fall. For some reason the only direction we can’t phase is down."

True to his word, you managed to take a seat, straightening your posture after recovering from the awkward endeavor of sitting in a chair you could not feel and looking at him expectantly. It's time for the interview to begin.

[[Continue.|Question 1:3]]
<img src="images/damien.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:1 {"position":"3200,2325","size":"100,100"}
You stand, having decided to use your time to explore the house a bit. Standing from your chair you take a few steps into the main entryway and see options before you of where to go. You could ascend the main stairs and explore the upper floors. You saw Damien head that way, which likely means that there are others up there as well. However it also means you might run into him. On the other hand, the manor is large, and there is plenty to explore on the ground floor as well.

[[Stay downstairs.|Explore 2:2:1:1]]
[[Go upstairs|Explore 2:2:2:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:1:1 {"position":"2950,2450","size":"100,100"}
You decide to stay downstairs and minimize the likelihood of running into Damien. With any luck, you'll arrive back before him and he'll be none the wiser.

You spend a few minutes at first just aimlessly wandering. You pass a variety of rooms – most emptied out or full of debris, but a few look usable and recently cleaned. That fact strikes you as odd. Infact, The entryway and the tea room where the first part of the interview was conducted were quite clean as well. You wonder how the other ghost's got it so clean? You doubted that any living people came here regularly to clean, and you hadn't been able to move anything since you died.

You pondered this thought as you wandered, until you were interrupted by the sound of hammering.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:2:1:2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:2:1 {"position":"3450,2450","size":"100,100"}
You walk up the stairs, simply hoping to avoid Damien while exploring the rooms up there. Most of the rooms on the second floor seem to be bedrooms, some with adjoining bathrooms. Many of them are in a sorry state of disrepair, but you stumble on a few that seem relatively clean and put together. You assume that these rooms belong to the other residents.

While you decidedly have less use for a bedroom than the living, the thought of having a space that was well and truly yours is very inviting. Especially if your room would be anything like these: they're quite nice.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:2:2:2]]
<img src="images/ghostbackground.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:1:2 {"position":"2950,2575","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $seenLydia to true>>
<<endsilently>>You round the corner and see another ghost – an older woman, with pale skin and grey hair in a long braid down her back. She's wearing a pair of overalls and a t-shirt, as well as a very worn pair of work gloves. More importantly, however, she's holding a hammer and using it to drive some nails into a beam that's splitting.

[["Hey! How are you doing that?" (Aggressive)|Explore 2:2:1:3 Aggressive]]
