:: Question 4:1 {"position":"2200,2775","size":"100,100"}
"So," Damien begins, "are you ready to continue our interview." You nod straightening in your chair.

Damien looks at you for a moment, brows knitting in confusion. Several times he opens his mouth to speak, before closing it again, seemingly thinking better of it. From his hesitancy, you could almost confuse him for the one being questioned.

"Are–" you begin, resolving to ask him what was the matter.

"What do you think the meaning of your life was?" he says, having come to a decision.

You balk a bit at his question. The rest of the interview was strange, but you could sort of see what the purpose of each question was. This however... what sort of housing interview was this?!

[["Seriously, what kind of question is that?!" (Aggressive)|Question 4:2 Aggressive]]
[["Survival." (Nervous)|Question 4:2 Nervous]]
[["I don't really believe in that." (Confident)|Question 4:2 Confident]]
[["Kindness." (Cheerful)|Question 4:2 Cheerful]]
<<if $listened>>[["Wait, is this about what the other ghost asked you to ask me?"|Question 4:2 Special]]<<endif>>

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:1:4 {"position":"2950,2825","size":"100,100"}
"I'm $name," you say.

"Huh," she says, looking you up and down. Then she simply shrugs. "We all can do it; move stuff, physical stuff at least. Ahmad figured it out first, then showed the rest of us. I'm the best at it though; like working with my hands."

"I didn't know ghosts could do that.." You reply. She simply nods.

"They can. Haven't you noticed Damien writing in that tiny notebook? How'd you think he was doing it?" She cocked her eyebrow.

You hadn't thought about it. The mention of Damien though reminds you of your time constraints. "Oh, I've actually got to go back..."

"Fine. See ya around." She waves you off and goes back to her repair work.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:3:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:3:1 {"position":"3075,3025","size":"100,100"}
You rush back to your seat in the tea room. The coast seems to be clear: Damien is nowhere in sight. Not ten seconds after you sit down, Damien rounds the corner and takes his seat as well, ready to begin the next part of the interview.

[[Continue.|Question 4:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:2:2 {"position":"3450,2575","size":"100,100"}
You walk down the twisting halls of the manor until your quiet stroll is interrupted by the sound of voices. Intrigued, you follow the sound until you find yourself standing in front of a closed door, presumably to a bedroom.

Just from where you're standing, you can make out two voices, but not what they're saying. One is clearly Damien – his voice is quite distinct, and after hearing it for the better part of an afternoon, you would recognize it anywhere. The other is very soft, barely above a whisper.

You have a decent guess what they're talking about: you. Damien said he was going to talk to the other residents about you; that is probably what this is.

[[Stay and listen at the door.|Explore 2:2:2:3:1]]
[[Wait until Damien leaves and go talk to the other voice.|Explore 2:2:2:3:2]]
[[Return and wait for the interview.|Explore 2:3:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:2:3:1 {"position":"3300,2700","size":"100,100"}
<<set $listened to true>>You get as close to the door as you can without accidentally phasing through it. The voices are still a bit muffled, but you are able to make out some of the words.

<<if $DamienOpinion gte 1>>"...you certain?" the quiet voice asks. There is a moment's pause before Damien answers. "Yes. They seem a trustworthy sort."

You feel a twinge of guilt at that.

The quieter voice does not reply for some time, but you hear a series of deep breaths, as if someone is trying to calm themself. After a few moments, the voice speaks, "Okay. I trust you. Could you try to figure out... maybe something that's important to them? Something from their life? If we're going to live with them, I'd like to try and get something for them."

"I'll do my best," Damien answers.<<else>>"...but you said–!" The quiet voice speaks, panic clear in their tone.

"I said I'm not certain, and I need to know more." Damien replies, voice a hushed whisper. "I was not certain about Lydia either, and she has been a wonderful house guest."

The quieter voice does not reply for some time, but you hear a series of deep breaths, as if someone is trying to calm themself. After a few moments, the voice speaks, "Okay. I trust you. Please just... be cautious. And could you ask... well, if we may still end up living with them... could you try to figure out something that's important to them? Something from their life? I'd like to try and get something for them, should they be permitted to stay."

"I'll do my best," Damien answers.<<endif>>

[[Continue.|Explore 2:3:2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:2:2:3:2 {"position":"3450,2700","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $seenJunia to true>>
<<endsilently>>It isn't long before Damien exits the room. He locks eyes with you, brows raised in surprise.

"I was waiting. Wanted to meet the potential housemates." You offer. When Damien doesn't immediately answer, you add, "I have to decide if I want to live here too, you know," feeling defensive.

Damien sighs and rolls his eyes, but you can see a bit of a smile on his face. "Junia!" he calls, voice raised so as to be easily heard but tone still even and steady, "You have a visitor!"

He walks off, and before long, a young looking woman phases through the door he just recently exited from. She shares the same skin and hair color as Damien, but with darker eyes. You wonder if they might have been related in life. Her dress looks similarly old fashioned as his suit.

"Oh!" she exclaims, seemingly quite startled to see a new face. "Oh, I wasn't... I-I mean I didn't expect you to... come up here. I suppose." Her eyes dart around, not staying on any one thing for longer than a few moments and pointedly not meeting yours.

[["What's wrong with you?" (Aggressive)|Exploration 2:2:2:4 Aggressive]]
[[You're having an equally hard time keeping the conversation up. (Nervous)|Exploration 2:2:2:4 Nervous]]
[["I'm touring the house." (Confident)|Exploration 2:2:2:4 Confident]]
[["It's nice to meet you!" (Cheerful)|Exploration 2:2:2:4 Cheerful]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:3:2 {"position":"3200,3025","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion -= 1>>
<<endsilently>>Several moments of silence pass before you realize that you won't be able to hear Damien's footsteps as he approaches the door. You are scarcely able to back away from the door before Damien phases through it. He looks surprised for a split second, and then his eyes harden into a cold fury. He bends down slightly to be at eye level with you, face no more than a few inches from your own.

"Privacy and honesty are very important to us, here," he nearly growls. He stands back to his full height and briskly walks down the hall for a moment before looking over his shoulder at you.

"Follow," he commands, and his harsh tone is so different from the odd impassivity you're used to that you comply without question. It isn't long before you're back at the table, sitting once more and waiting to begin the next part of the interview.

[[Continue.|Question 4:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Exploration 2:2:2:4 Aggressive {"position":"3250,2825","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion -= 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I-I'm sorry?!"

You close your eyes and take a deep breath. Clearly that didn't go over well. "I mean," you say, "why are you unwilling to look at me? I'm just another ghost, same as you."

"I-I'm sorry, Ishould just... I'll go." She says, before practically running through the door she just emerged from.

It's clearly not worth it to follow her – she doesn't want to talk to you. That interaction certainly isn't helping your opinion of the house.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:3:3]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Exploration 2:2:2:4 Nervous {"position":"3375,2825","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"Oh, sorry, I was just... I wanted to explore the house a bit. Meet the people I might be living with," you say looking to the side. Under your breath you add, "make sure everyone is... y'know friendly, I guess."

Junia seems to have heard you. You catch her smiling lightly, though still not meeting your eyes. "I suppose that's... sort of what we're doing with this interview," she adds. If anything, your mutual discomfort seems to be giving her more confidence.

After a moment, she takes a breath, steels herself, and meets your eye. "I'm Junia. You have met my brother, Damien. It's nice to meet you."

You smile. "Thank you; it's nice to meet you as well."

"Uh, not to cut this short but... isn't he waiting for you?"

Your eyes go wide at the realization. "Right! Thanks, I'll see you later."

Junia nods and you dart off down the hall.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:3:3]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Exploration 2:2:2:4 Confident {"position":"3500,2825","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion -= 1>>
<<endsilently>>Junia doesn't respond; she just continues to look away from you. "I was hoping to meet the residents, get a sense for the place." You add, pointedly. You hope this 'Junia' will get the message and introduce herself.

She does not.

After several more moments of deeply uncomfortable silence, you sigh, loudly, and say, "Well, I have to get back to the interview. It was lovely speaking with you."

She nods and offers a quiet "Goodbye" before rushing back through the door.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:3:3]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Exploration 2:2:2:4 Cheerful {"position":"3625,2825","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I'm trying to meet some of the residents of the house," you say, but the explanation of your presence doesn't seem to bring any comfort to Junia. If anything, she seems more nervous. Your brow furrows and you offer a soft smile. "Sorry if I'm intruding," you add. "I can go if you like."

"No, uh... it's okay," Junia finally says. "Sorry, if I was rude. I'm Junia, Damien's sister."

"Oh I had no idea he had a sister! Well, like I said, it's lovely to meet you. I hope we can chat again soon, but I think your brother is waiting on me!" You say, smiling at her as you turn to walk away.

Junia does look relieved that the conversation is over, but she doesn't seem as if she was wholly unhappy with meeting you.

[[Continue.|Explore 2:3:3]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2:3:3 {"position":"3325,3025","size":"100,100"}
You make your way back to the tea room to find Damien, expectedly, waiting for you. He gestures at your seat and you oblige him. Once you are settled, he looks at you ready to begin the next part of this interview.

[[Continue.|Question 4:1]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 2 Wait {"position":"2200,2650","size":"100,100"}
You decide to stay seated, not wanting to anger your benefactor or hurt your chances of living here. Time passes slowly in the silence of the manor, and you start to regret your choice before long. Just as you're considering taking a quick peek around, Damien rounds the corner. He offers you a slight, appreciative smile, presumably for having followed his instructions, and takes his seat.

[[Continue.|Question 4:1]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 4:2 Aggressive {"position":"2000,2900","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $aggressive += 1>>
<<set $DamienOpinion -= 1>>
<<endsilently>>"What, you need to know if my 'grand purpose' is good enough for your falling-apart house?"

Damiens lips purse and a coldness enters his eyes. "It was simply something one of the housemates wished to know. You needn't be so rude."

"Right," You say, rolling your eyes, "I'm the rude one here. Why couldn't this 'housemate' ask me themself?"

Damien opens his mouth to answer, but you cut him off. You've had enough of this. "Oh right, I'm sorry, I'm not supposed to meet any of the others! Only you get to evaluate me, right?"

Damien closes his eyes and takes several deep breaths. Finally, he looks at you and says, "Your concerns are noted. Let's move on."

[[Continue.|Question 5:1]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 4:2 Nervous {"position":"2125,2900","size":"100,100"}
"I guess... the meaning of life is to keep living? So, you know, doing what you can to survive," you say, feeling profoundly awkward.

Damien cocks an eyebrow. "That doesn't leave you with much now, does it?" he says. You have a hard time telling if he's being condescending or genuinely curious.

"N-no. No it doesn't."

Damien nods, and you move on to the next question.

[[Continue.|Question 5:1]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 4:2 Confident {"position":"2275,2900","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>You furrow your brow in thought for a moment. "I don't really see it that way," you say, after a moment's pause. "I don't think I had a purpose or meaning or anything of the sort. I don't really think anyone does. We're all just... people, living out lives. We may each find meaning in what matters to us, what we choose to prioritize, but that doesn't mean it's what makes our lives important. We were alive; that's meaning enough."

Damien's eyebrows raise in mild surprise. "Well said," he responds simply, and jots something down in his notebook.

[[Continue.|Question 5:1]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 4:2 Cheerful {"position":"2400,2900","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I would say that, in life, I strove to make the world a little bit better than I found it. I hope I was successful," you say.

Damien gives you a soft smile. "And now?" he asks, one eyebrow cocked.

"We're all still 'living', even if we're dead. I don't see any reason to stop trying to be kind."

Damien nods, a smile still on his face.

[[Continue.|Question 5:1]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 5:1 {"position":"2200,3025","size":"100,100"}
"Well, for our final question," Damien began, steepling his fingers, "I wanted to know what skills you gathered in life that may be useful for us here?"

"I'm... not sure what you mean?" you respond. <<if $seenLydia>>"I know some ghosts can move things, but I haven't been able to do anything like that since I died."<<else>>"I mean, I'm a ghost, it's not like I can do much."<<endif>>

"There are ways of learning to... interact more concretely with the world," Damien explains. "The spirits who reside here could help you learn them. But regardless, there are skills beyond physical. Just tell me a bit about what you were particularly good at in life. Perhaps there's a way for you to contribute that we haven't considered yet."

[[Physical Skills|Question 5.2.1]]
[[Technical Skills|Question 5.2.2]]
[[Rhetorical Skills|Question 5.2.3]]
[[Artistic Skills|Question 5.2.4]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 4:2 Special {"position":"2075,2775","size":"100,100"}
Damien sighs, loudly. He closes his eyes and rubs the bridge of his nose.

"Just... answer the question, please."

[["But what kind of question is that?!" (Aggressive)|Question 4:2 Aggressive]]
[["Survival." (Nervous)|Question 4:2 Nervous]]
[["I don't really believe in that." (Confident)|Question 4:2 Confident]]
[["Kindness." (Cheerful)|Question 4:2 Cheerful]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 5.2.1 {"position":"2000,3150","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $LydiaOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I was always pretty active. Decent with my hands, building stuff, that sort of thing."

Damien nods. "Well the house is always in need of repairs. We have another spirit here who takes care of most of that. I'm sure she would appreciate some help."<<if $seenLydia>> You had a feeling you knew who he was talking about.<<endif>>

[[Continue.|Explore 3 Choice]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 5.2.2 {"position":"2125,3150","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I was always good with technical things. Had a head for numbers, decent with computers. Stuff like that."

Damien's face flashed a nervous expression. "A-ah, yes... well it's been quite some time since anyone new has joined the house. Many years in fact. Those of us here... don't really know much about all of that. It would probably be good to have someone here who does."

You smiled, knowing that your answer made you somewhat of a commodity here. Perhaps that would increase your chances.

[[Continue.|Explore 3 Choice]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 5.2.3 {"position":"2275,3150","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"Well, I've always been quite good with words," You offer. "Reading, writing, and speaking I would say are particular skills of mine, as well keeping a level head when put on the spot, and finding a way to make complex ideas more accessible."

"Quite the valuable skill," Damien adds. "And one that is in no way fettered by your spectral state. There is another spirit here who I feel you might get on well with. He's certainly the most talkative of us."<<if $seenAhmad>>

You wonder if he's talking about the man you saw in the window earlier...<<endif>>

[[Continue.|Explore 3 Choice]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Question 5.2.4 {"position":"2400,3150","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I always considered myself something of an artist," you offer. "I've experimented with quite a few different mediums, and I honestly love any sort of visual art, both creating it and experiencing it."

You look down at your hands, forlorn. "Honestly one of the worst parts of being dead is not having been able to make anything any more..."

"Do not worry, all of us here have attained some ability to manipulate objects. It may be difficult, but we can teach you to create again." Damien offers with a smile."Besides, you are not the only artist in our midst."

"Oh?" you say, an unmistakable question.

Damien obliges you. <<if $seenJunia>>"Junia, whom you met upstairs. I'm sure the two of you will have much to talk about."<<else>>"There is another spirit here, Junia. She is quite the artist herself. I'm sure she would be happy to help you adjust to creating without a physical body."<<endif>>

[[Continue.|Explore 3 Choice]]

<img src="images/damien1.png" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3 Choice {"position":"2200,3275","size":"100,100"}
"And... I believe that is all." Damien stands. Before you can speak, he continues. "I need to speak with some of the others for a moment. I won't be long, and then the five of us, including you, will conclude the interview. You... may explore the estate a bit, but please do not keep us waiting long. Once we're ready, we will meet you here and then adjourn to the dining hall to finish the interview and make our decision. Do you have any questions?"

You balk a bit at Damien's tone. He hasn't been the most relaxed person this entire time, but he seems even more stiff and formal now. You wonder why that is...

"No, I'm good." you reply. He gives you a stiff nod and then walks away, this time down a hallway on the ground level.

You realize you have some time to kill, and think to yourself about what to do with it.

[[Explore a bit.|Explore 3:1]]
[[Stay put.|Explore 3:2]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:1 {"position":"1800,3425","size":"100,100"}
You decide your time is better spent being up and around, exploring the house a bit. <<if $DamienOpinion gte 1>>You have a pretty good feeling about the interview, so it makes sense to get to know what is likely to be your new home.<<else>>You aren't feeling super confident about how this interview is going. Perhaps walking around will clue you in on something that will help with the last part.<<endif>>

Without really realizing it, you find yourself wandering in the direction that Damien had left in. After only a few moments of wandering, you begin to hear voices – raised voices.

[[Continue.|Explore 3:1:2]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:2 {"position":"2600,3425","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $seenAhmad2 = true>>
<<endsilently>>You decide to sit for a while and simply enjoy the quiet. You need a moment of respite before the end of the interview, anyway. <<if $DamienOpinion gte 1>>You have a pretty good feeling about the interview, but that doesn't mean it isn't stressful!<<else>>You aren't feeling super confident about how this interview is going, and you brace for the worst.<<endif>>

However, not long after Damien left, you see another ghost coming down the stairs and approaching your table.<<if $seenAhmad>>You recognise him: he's the man who was waving to you from the window earlier.<<else>>He is a younger looking man – dark brown skin, short cropped hair, and dark eyes.<<endif>> The ghost approaches and sits down where Damien had been sitting previously.

"Hello!" he says, voice chipper like songbirds.

"Oh, uh, hello," you reply, almost startled by his friendliness. 'Friendly' isn't exactly the vibe you've gotten from this place so far.

"I'm Ahmad, one of the ghosts who lives here. You must be the one interviewing!" he continues.

"Yes, that's me. I'm $name."

<<if $seenAhmad>><<if $AhmadOpinion gt 0>>"Well, I hope you get in!" hey says, a wide grin on his face.<<else>>"Well, it's good to meet you in person!" he says, smiling.<<endif>><<else>>"Well, it's good to meet you!" he says, smiling.<<endif>>

You smile back, his cheer practically infectious.

[[Continue.|Explore 3:2:2]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:1:2 {"position":"1800,3550","size":"100,100"}
<<if $seenLydia>><<set $seenJunia = true>>"Why not?!" You hear a shout in a familiar voice. You round the corner and see three figures in a room with an open door. The first is Damien, tall but hardly imposing in comparison with the person standing to his left. That person you recognise as Lydia, who you met in the hallway before. It must have been her who shouted. The argument they're having seems quite heated. Lydia particularly looks very angry.

You almost don't notice the third person in the room. She's a young looking woman, and seeing her and Damien side by side, you almost think they might be related. She seems to be trying to make herself as invisible as possible while the other two ghosts argue.

"I mean honestly WHAT is the point!?" Lydia continues. You're surprised by her temper, she seemed almost painfully neutral when you spoke earlier.

"The point," Damien says, spitting the last word with barely contained venom, "is to protect all of us."

"By all of us, you mean Junia." Lydia gestures over to the other ghost. "You know it's been centuries right? Your sister can probably handle herself."

So they were related.

"I don't want to be protected!" Junia speaks up, surprising Damien. "I want to be involved. The easiest way of keeping us all safe is to have us ALL involved in the vetting process."

"Safe," Lydia replies, scoffing at the notion. "Safe from what? Need I remind you we're all dead? It's not like anything can really hurt us."

"That's not true, Lydia!" the quiet woman on the right speaks up, surprising the other two ghosts. "We have a peaceful and comfortable existence here. That's worth protecting!"

Damien finally notices you and locks eyes. "It seems we have a visitor."

"Great. Oi! You, new ghost!" Lydia calls over to you. "Let's hear your thoughts."

"They are obviously a biased source." Damine says, rolling his eyes.

"Exactly," Lydia replies. "They're affected by this, they should get a say. so, new ghost, let's hear it."
<<elseif $seenJunia>><<set $seenLydia = true>>"Why not?!" You hear a shout in an unfamiliar voice. You round the corner and see three figures in a room with an open door. The first is Damien, tall but hardly imposing in comparison with the person standing to his left. The person to his left is an older woman, with pale skin and grey hair in a long braid down her back. She's wearing a pair of overalls and a t-shirt, as well as a very worn pair of work gloves. The argument they're having seems quite heated. The woman in particular looks very angry.

You almost don't notice the third person in the room, but you instantly recognize her as Junia, from upstairs. She seems to be trying to make herself as invisible as possible while the other two ghosts argue.

