:: Explore 3:1:3 Aggressive {"position":"1600,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion -= 1>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion -= 1>>
<<set $LydiaOpinion += 1>>
<<set $aggressive += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"This is an excuse for people with a lot of resources," you say, "gesturing around at the massive house, "to hoard them and hold them over everyone else!"

"But... that's not..." Damien starts. He and Junia both look quite upset. Both guilty and frustrated.

"Well said," Lydia pipes up. "And as someone that's been on the other side of the table, I can tell you that's exactly what it feels like."

"But it's not about hoarding!" Junia shouts. "It's about making sure that if we let someone in, it won't be someone who'll be cruel to us. It's not like we can really get rid of them, and we don't want to live in fear and discomfort for eternity!"

"You have to trust people more than–" Lydia starts, before being interrupted by Damien.

"Enough!" he shouts, silencing her. "The interview is in progress and we are almost finished. Since we're all together, we may as well grab Ahmad and get started. No doubt he's waiting for us already."

Damien gestures for everyone to exit the room, but turns to speak to the other two ghosts under his breath. "We will finish this discussion afterwards..."

