:: Explore 3:1:3 Confident {"position":"1875,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion += 1>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion -= 1>>
<<set $LydiaOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"I mean, you wouldn't want someone to take over your home, especially someone who wouldn't treat you and yours with respect."

Damien smiles at you. "I appreciate your understanding in this."

Lydia, on the other hand, just rolls her eyes and crosses her arms. "If you're fine being 'evaluated', who am I to judge?"

Junia, however, looks deeply frustrated. "S-so you're fine with the interview process but aren't willing to hear me out about meeting us all upfront?"

Before you can answer, Damien steps in. "Regardless, the last part of the interview is collaborative. We may as well finish up before deciding anything moving forward." Junia sighs but says nothing in protest, and Damien turns to the rest of us.

"Well" Damien begins, "the interview is in progress and we are almost finished. Since we're all together, we may as well grab Ahmad and get started. No doubt he's waiting for us already."

