:: Explore 3:1:3 Cheerful {"position":"2000,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienOpinion -= 1>>
<<set $JuniaOpinion += 1>>
<<set $LydiaOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"If the whole point of this is to make sure you all would be comfortable, then it makes more sense for everyone to meet the new person upfront, rather than for you to act as a middleman."

Junia gives you a warm smile. "I appreciate you taking my side in this."

Lydia sighs. "A fair enough compromise, if you aren't bent out of shape about the interview, then I guess I don't have any reason to argue about it... for now."

Damien, however, does not look convinced. "I do this so that if anyone is... particularly unpleasant, you all do not have to deal with that."

"I-I appreciate that," Junia says, "but we can handle it. It's... better to be informed than to simply sit and worry."

"Well" Damien begins shaking his head, "the interview is in progress and we are almost finished. Since we're all together, we may as well grab Ahmad and get started. No doubt he's waiting for us already."

Damien gestures for everyone to exit the room, but turns to speak to the other two ghosts under his breath. "We will finish this discussion afterwards..."

