:: Explore 3:1:4 {"position":"1800,3800","size":"100,100"}
The four of us walk back to where we held the first part of the interview, to find someone waiting for us there.<<if $seenAhmad>> The man you had seen in the window earlier sits in Damien's seat.<<else>> Another ghost, who you presume to be Ahmad based on Damien's comments, sits in Damien's seat. He is a younger looking man – dark brown skin, short cropped hair, and dark eyes.<<endif>> Ahmad smiles warmly at the group, and falls in line with the rest of you wordlessly.

You continue to walk until you reach what is clearly a large dining hall. You all take various sets around the table, and all eyes turn to you.

[[Continue|Interview End 1]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:2:2 {"position":"2600,3550","size":"100,100"}
"So..." you begin, unsure of how to keep up the conversation. "Was the interview the same when you did it?"

"When I..." Ahmad says, confused. Then his face lights up in recognition. "Oh! No, sorry, I never interviewed. This is my house."

You look at him, a bit taken aback. "But... I thought Damien..."

"No," Ahmad responds, waving the notion off with his hand. "Damien and his sister were the first to move in after me. I let Damien do this whole interview thing because he and his sister are a bit uncomfortable around most people. Took them ages to get used to Lydia, and that was after Damien decided to let her in."

"They're more worried about things changing than me," he continued. "I can get along with just about anyone."

You aren't sure what to say to this revelation.

[["But... why do you let him boss you around?" (Aggressive)|Explore 3:3:3 Aggressive]]
[["S-so... You're the one I really have to impress." (Nervous)|Explore 3:3:3 Nervous]]
[["All of this is mainly for Damien's benefit?" (Confident)|Explore 3:3:3 Confident]]
[["That's rather nice of you." (Cheerful)|Explore 3:3:3 Cheerful]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:3:3 Aggressive {"position":"2400,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $aggressive += 1>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>Ahmad chuckles lightly. "I don't"

You raise an eyebrow, unconvinced. Ahmad leans forward, ready to explain.

"I let him vet people because he's my friend, and his comfort matters. If there's someone I really want to be here, I can usually convince him."

You remain unconvinced.

[[Continue.|Explore 3:2:4]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:3:3 Nervous {"position":"2525,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>Ahmad lets out a hearty laugh. "No, no. Nothing like that."

He leans forward and clasps his hands. "I'm not interested in turning people away."

You furrow your brow. "Then... why do you?"

He raises an eyebrow and you realize your mistake. "I mean, I know it's Damien doing the interviews but... you still let him turn people away."

Ahmad smiles, but his eyes grow a bit distant. Then he leans closer and says, "Can I tell you a secret?"

You nod, and he continues, "We've never turned anyone away. Tensions are so high right now because you're the only person aside from Lydia that's asked to stay."

You look at him, confused. That can't be right, can it?

[[Continue.|Explore 3:2:4]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:3:3 Confident {"position":"2675,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"Well, him and his sister," Ahmad corrects. He shrugs his shoulders. "Look, Damien's reasoning is sound. People can be really fragile after they die. Before too. We all have different needs. For him and Junia, that need is security and agency. They need to feel like they're safe and in control. If this interview helps with that, then so be it."

Ahmad leans back, clearly satisfied with himself. You aren't entirely sure what to make of this information.

[[Continue.|Explore 3:2:4]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:3:3 Cheerful {"position":"2800,3675","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<endsilently>>"Aw, well thank you." Ahmad says, surprised.

"I mean it. You're trying to make them feel safe. That's admirable," you say, sincerity clear in your voice.

"I'm glad you understand," Ahmad says. "And I like your chances of staying here," he adds with a wink.

[[Continue.|Explore 3:2:4]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Explore 3:2:4 {"position":"2600,3800","size":"100,100"}
Before you can ponder much of what Ahmad tells you, you see three ghosts approaching you. <<if $seenLydia>>Damien is in the front, followed by Lydia, who you met earlier. Behind them is another ghost you haven't seen. She looks like a young woman, with a similar skin and hair color as Damien, wearing a similarly old fashioned dress.<<elseif $seenJunia>>Damien is in the front, followed by another ghost you haven't met. She looks like an older woman, with pale skin and a long braid of gray hair down her back, wearing overalls and a t-shirt. Behind them is a third ghost, who you recognise as Junia.<<else>>Damien is in the front, followed by two other ghosts you haven't met. The first looks like an older woman, with pale skin and a long braid of gray hair down her back, wearing overalls and a t-shirt. Behind them is another ghost, who looks like a young woman, with a similar skin and hair color as Damien, wearing a similarly old fashioned dress.<<endif>>

"Ah," Damien says. "It's just about time to conclude our interview. If you two will follow me..."

You continue to walk until you reach what is clearly a large dining hall. You all take various sets around the table, and all eyes turn to you.

[[Continue|Interview End 1]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Interview End 1 {"position":"2200,3900","size":"100,100"}
"So, $name," Damien begins, steepling his fingers, "We have discussed amongst ourselves and I believe we have come to a decision." The air hangs thick with tension, anticipation. "But..." he continues "it is also worth noting that this process has been... rather one sided. I have asked you questions on behalf of the residents here, but you haven't had much of a chance to sate your own curiosity. So, as a group, we would like to have an open discussion. You may ask us questions, be they about the house or about ourselves, and we will endeavor to answer as truthfully as possible. At the same time, think of this as... a final moment to plead your case, if you will. This discussion may change our decision, or it may not, but it will likely be helpful in you deciding whether or not to accept an offer of residence here, should one be given. Does that all sound amenable to you?"

You ponder Damien's speech for a moment, before nodding in acceptance. "Sure," you respond, racking your brain for questions to ask.

"Very well," Damien says, "Ask what you will."

<<if not $DamienQuestion>>[["Damien, why go through this whole process?"|Damien Question 1]]<<else>>=="Damien, why go through this whole process?"==<<endif>>
<<if not $JuniaQuestion>><<if $seenJunia>>[["Junia, what is it about this place that makes you happy?"|Junia Question 1]]<<else>>[[Address the quiet seeming ghost who looks similar to Damien.|Junia Question 2]]<<endif>><<else>><<if $seenJunia>>=="Junia, what is it about this place that makes you happy?"==<<else>>==Address the quiet seeming ghost who looks similar to Damien.==<<endif>><<endif>>
<<if not $LydiaQuestion>><<if $seenLydia>>[["Lydia, how did you learn to do the whole... moving stuff thing?"|Lydia Question 1]]<<else>>[[Address the stern seeming ghost with the long silver braid.|Lydia Question 2]]<<endif>><<else>><<if $seenLydia>>=="Lydia, how did you learn to do the whole... moving stuff thing?"==<<else>>==Address the stern seeming ghost with the long silver braid.==<<endif>><<endif>>
<<if not $AhmadQuestion>><<if $seenAhmad>>[["Ahmad, did you get any say in the decision?"|Ahmad Question 1]]<<else>>[[Address the cheerful seeming, young looking ghost.|Ahmad Question 2]]<<endif>><<else>><<if $seenAhmad>>=="Ahmad, did you get any say in the decision?"==<<else>>==Address the cheerful seeming, young looking ghost.==<<endif>><<endif>>
[["I think I'm ready to hear your decision."|Endings]]
[["I think I'm just going to go."|Ending 4]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Damien Question 1 {"position":"1275,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $DamienQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>Damien raises an eyebrow at your question. He takes a long moment to ponder before answering.

"As I've said at various points, it is my job to look after the residents of this house - to help ensure that their afterlives are as peaceful and happy as they can be."

"But, it isn't though, I mean, not directly." Damien looks confused at your remark. You continue, "I mean, we're all dead. it's not like you're getting a paycheck. You're obviously doing this because you think it's meaningful. So why? And why do the interview rather than like, hiding where you live as best you can?"

"I see. It was... difficult, before me and Junia moved in. We wanted to make sure this place remains safe... but it also feels like the right thing to give other people the chance we were offered."

He pauses for a moment before asking. "If you were in my position, would you not do the same?"

[["Yes, I think I would."|Damien Question 1:1]]
[["No, I would simply provide shelter to anyone who needs it."|Damien Question 1:2]]
[["No, I would hold on to what's mine."|Damien Question 1:3]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Junia Question 1 {"position":"1675,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>"It's certainly... more peaceful than wandering amongst the living who can't see you and the other ghosts, fighting over places to haunt."

You find you agree with her.

Junia looks to the side, seemingly debating in herself whether or not to continue. After a moment, she looks up at you.

"I suppose the main draw is... security. Safety, even. I know what my days will look like, and who I will spend them with. Safety is strange when you're dead. Physically, nothing can hurt you. But you also have a very limited ability to control the world around you. That lack of control is... frightening. I guess that's what this house offers. Some safety and control."

[["The house doesn't really protect you though."|Junia Question 1:1]]
[["That sounds lovely."|Junia Question 1:2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Junia Question 2 {"position":"1800,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $JuniaQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>"So," you begin, turning your head towards the comparatively timid woman sitting next to Damien. "Do you mind if I ask you about yourself?"

The woman looks around before settling her eyes on you, pointing to herself as if asking, 'Me?' You nod, incredulously, and the ghost stumbles over herself to respond.

"O-oh, my name is Junia." She pauses, clearly trying to decide if that was enough of an answer. You look at her, expectantly, as the moments of awkward silence drag on. She visibly gulps before continuing, "I'm Damien's sister. I've been here... well, as long as he has, in any case."

"Do you like it here?" you ask, not knowing what other questions you could derive from her rather sparse answer.

The ghost nods. "Yes, I do. It's certainly... more peaceful than wandering amongst the living who can't see you and the other ghosts, fighting over places to haunt."

You find you agree with her.

[[Continue.|Interview End 2]]

<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Lydia Question 1 {"position":"2600,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $LydiaQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>Lydia chuckles. "That's what you wanna use your question on?"

You simply shrug. "It seems important, especially if I don't end up living here."

Lydia nods solemnly. "Well that I can't help with."

"What do you mean?" you ask, concerned.

"I can't really help you move things if you don't live here," Lydia explains nonchalantly.

[["Why not?"|Lydia Question 1:1]]
[["Can't or won't?"|Lydia Question 1:2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Lydia Question 2 {"position":"2725,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $LydiaQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>You turn to the tough looking older woman with the long silver hair. "So, uh, who are you?"

She merely raises an eyebrow at you. After a moment, she replies, "Lydia." You continue staring at her, waiting for her to continue. She stares back, silently.

"Uhh...?" you start, before she rolls her eyes and continues.

"I live here," she says, as if it's obvious. To her credit, it is. Damien coughs awkwardly.

"Lydia is our most recent resident here, and the first to do the interview process," he offers, by way of explanation. Lydia simply nods.

"Was the interview... like this, last time?" you ask, hoping to get a little more information out of her. To your surprise, she cracks a small smile.

"Yeah."

[[Continue.|Interview End 2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Ahmad Question 1 {"position":"3125,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadOpinion += 1>>
<<set $AhmadQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>"Oh don't worry about it," Ahmad waves you off. "They don't need to ask my opinion. They know I'll just vote yes."

You shrug. That seems pretty on point after your conversation with him. At least you know you have one supporter. You smile at him and return to your questioning.

[[Continue.|Interview End 2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


:: Ahmad Question 2 {"position":"3250,4000","size":"100,100"}
<<silently>>
<<set $AhmadQuestion to true>>
<<endsilently>>You turn to the young looking man, sitting farthest from Damien, and ask, "What's your name?"

He smiles at you, excitedly and answers almost before you've finished asking the question. "I'm Ahmad!" he says, practically beaming. "I was the owner of this house, y'know, back when I was alive."

"Wait," you say, puzzled, "I thought this was Damien's house?"

Ahmad lets out a bemused chuckle. "No, I just let him and Junia move it years ago."

"Well, then why isn't it you doing the interviews?" you ask, trying to keep the irritation out of your voice.

"Because," he says, smiling, "I don't want to."

[[Continue|Interview End 2]]
<img src="images/intro1.jpeg" width="512" height="512">


